ation rate of >~ 20%.\nThese candidates are at lower Eddington ratio relative to the overall quasar\npopulation which supports a disk-wind model for the broad line region. Based on\nour sample, the CLQ fraction increases from 10% to roughly half as the\ncontinuum flux ratio between repeat spectra at 3420 Angstroms increases from\n1.5 to 6. We release a catalog of over 200 highly variable candidates to\nfacilitate future CLQ searches.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Sep 2018 21:23:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2019 22:25:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-20"}
